headline: American Airlines Reports Earnings Tuesday. What the Stock Needs to Fly Through the Storm.
summary: Wall Street is watching to see if  American Airlines  can beat expectations when the carrier reports its earnings before the open Tuesday.  Another aviation giant,  United  beat fourth-quarter predictions last week, boosting the stock—investors will hope American can do the same.  Analysts are expecting adjusted earnings per share of 37 cents on revenue of $14 billion in the fourth quarter, according to FactSet data.

headline: Air travel will return to normal by Wednesday, Transportation Secretary Duffy says
summary: Transportation Secretary Sean Duffy told CNBC that air travel should be back to normal by Wednesday, following a significant disruption from the snowstorm.
